critique: This document is an executive order that amends a previous executive order related to the Agricultural Trade Development and Assistance Act of 1934. It removes some text and a paragraph from the previous order. Because it deals with agricultural trade and assistance, it has some economic implications. However, without the text of the original order, it is difficult to assess the full impact of these changes. It does not seem to directly address immigration, executive power, federalism, national security, or social inclusion. The changes seem technical in nature.
